CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper May 11, 1957, pg. 14, reads: "25 Years of Song - One of the features of the program sponsored by Wesley Center Cathedral Choir was an honorarium, citing members who have served 25 years or more. They are, standing, left to right: Charles Fields, Nathan Youngblood, Mrs. Ada Woodson and Robert Pamon. Seated, left: Mrs. Lula Hatcher, and Mrs. Clara Harrold. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of Wesley Center AME Zion Church choir standing from left: Charles Fields, Nathan Youngblood, Ada Woodson, Robert Pamon; seated: Lula Hatcher and Clara Harrold posed in church
